The developers cited production issues and a desire to focus on the next installment, FM26, as the reasons for the cancellation. Fans of the popular football management simulation game expressed disappointment, but the developers offered apologies and refunds for pre-orders. The reasons behind the cancellation remain unclear, with Sports Interactive simply stating that they are prioritizing the quality of future releases. name: Liverpool vs Tottenham
summary: Liverpool and Tottenham Hotspur faced off in the second leg of their Carabao Cup semi-final, with Liverpool securing a 4-1 victory to advance to the final with a 4-1 aggregate score. The match was closely contested, with Tottenham taking an early lead through Harry Kane. However, Liverpool rallied to score four unanswered goals from Diogo Jota, Roberto Firmino, Takumi Minamino, and Trent Alexander-Arnold. The win marks Liverpool's sixth victory in seven matches against Tottenham, and puts them into the final of the Carabao Cup for the ninth time in the past 13 years. Tottenham's defeat means they have now lost three consecutive matches and will need to regroup ahead of their Premier League clash with Manchester City.

name: Bank of England base rate
summary: Interest rates have been a focus of discussion lately, with the Bank of England making several adjustments to its base rate in recent months. Due to economic concerns, the central bank has cut rates twice in the past six months, bringing it down to 4.5%, the lowest level since 2023. This has led to questions about when and how quickly rates might fall further, with the market anticipating another rate cut in February. Experts within the financial industry provide insights into the potential implications of these changes, particularly in relation to mortgages and the economy as a whole. Additionally, the government has announced revisions to its late payment interest rates, aligning them with the Bank of England's base rate adjustments.
